  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Students) Enhanced understanding of the importance of (universal values such as) acceptance, tolerance, inclusion, gender equality and inclusion among young people selected communities.  Teachers have improved their teaching proficiency using new student focused methodologies and mainstreaming gender in their methodologies. New student focused methodologies, including core skills (break them down) enhancement are embedded into the school curriculum and English language clubs are supported by communities and local education structures (beyond the life of project)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. School pupils in isolated communities. 
2. English teachers of isolated communities.</narrative>
  </description>
